The paper deals with resource allocation algorithm design for multicarrier non-orthogonal multiple access (MC-NOMA) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm aims to maximize the system throughput, which is a system-level optimization problem and falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also involves simulation results, which may fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories.
